  "prompt": "What do I do if my best friend is dating my crush?",
  "response": "This is a difficult situation. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Be honest with your feelings\n- Talk to your friend about how you feel\n- Communicate openly and calmly\n- Try to understand their perspective\n\n2. Process your emotions\n- Allow yourself to feel hurt or disappointed\n- Don't blame yourself or your friend\n- Give yourself time to heal\n\n3. Maintain the friendship\n- Try not to let this damage your relationship\n- Be supportive if possible\n- Avoid being passive-aggressive\n\n4. Focus on yourself\n- Work on personal growth\n- Pursue your own interests\n- Meet new people\n- Remember that there are other potential romantic partners\n\n5. Consider distance if needed\n- If the situation is too painful, it's okay to take some space\n- Limit interactions temporarily if necessary\n\n6. Learn and move forward\n- Use this as an opportunity for personal development\n- Keep a positive attitude\n- Stay open to new relationships\n\nRemember, how you handle this situation says a lot about your character and maturity.",
